AB  - This paper develops a number of concepts of trade expenditure functions for an internationally trading economy with many households which differ in tastes and factor endowments. These concepts are then applied to the analysis of gains from trade in undistorted economies with and without governmental intervention. We generalise and extend a number of propositions concerning sufficient, and necessary and sufficient conditions for individual households and groups of households to gain from trade in economies which are subject to trade taxes and subsidies.
