AB  - In lieu of a fictitious Walrasian auctioneer, price determination in a simple two-country two-good trade model is explicitly modelled as the strategic price-setting behavior of merchants. The results depend on the order in which countries are visited and whether or not the supply is backward-bending. Theorem 1 establishes sufficient conditions for the Walrasian outcome to be the unique subgame perfect Nash equilibrium (SPNE). Theorem 2 shows when the unique SPNE is non-Walrasian.
