AB  - Labor market conditions can have important effects on imperfectly competitive rivalries between firms. This paper examines the consequences of unionization for the rivalry between duopoly firms in an international environment, using the generalized Nash bargaining solution to determine the wage, and the (noncooperative) Nash equilibrium to determine the output equilibrium. The paper analyzes the trade policy incentives resulting from unionization, focusing on profit shifting tariffs, quotas and subsidies.
